    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Auto-post the content calendar with Google Drive and WordPress for your team\n\n**Pattern:** Social Scheduler · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nAuto-post the content calendar with Google Drive and WordPress for your team. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual scheduling is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Stamp & Shape Post → Payload Valid? → Build the Brief → Draft with AI Writer → Refine with AI Editor → Publish Draft to WordPress → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to social scheduler without manual effort\n- Anyone automating scheduling in marketing\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2 / service account; OpenAI API key; Slack OAuth2; WordPress credentials.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "fe7f90f2-27d3-5d97-4f7d-5f3d3178bcb3",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "1fddb3bb-1566-e534-0fdc-b1cda5fc415c",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
